This paper primarily focuses on the security of audit logs in enterprise business systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also leverages blockchain technology to ensure the tamper-proof nature of the audit logs, which relates to database systems (cs.DB) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The implementation and evaluation of the system involve network and system performance, which falls under the categories of distributed systems (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
